Date:  0/0/1978
Source:  Oxford Book of NZ Plants
Author:  MOORE & IRWIN
Vol / Page:  22
Edition:
Quote:  <i>PERSOONIA (TORONIA) TORU.</i> Toru is common in the north and extends to the Volcanic Plateau where it can be seen ... on Rainbow Mountain. ... `The name is derived from the epithet toru, of Maori origin, and the ending <i>-onia</i> to suggest the affinity with <i>Persoonia'. (Johnson and Briggs 1975).
